                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d793">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.9411/126: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-25T18:00:00+09:00"
                            >April 25, 1941—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 25—10:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>602. The following information has been obtained from a reliable source:</p>
                <p>The Black Dragon Society, which is both anti-Fascist and anti-Communist, sent a
                    delegation to call on Mr. Matsuoka immediately after his return to Tokyo from
                    Moscow and put to him a series of interrogatories with regard to the extent of
                    the agreement which he had concluded at Moscow. Mr. Matsuoka gave the most
                    categorical assurances that the Japanese-Soviet neutrality treaty contained no
                    secret clauses, that the complete text of all documents signed or agreed upon
                    had been published, and that no oral engagement of any kind was given either by
                    Japan or the Soviet Union. He added that the question of the signatories
                    reducing their respective military forces in [Manchuria?] and in Siberia had not
                    even been discussed.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Moscow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
